author: Cleo Abram
description:
I’ve been cheering at the wrong moment during a rocket launch… 

No! I mean, incredibly cool, but  for the engineers, they’re still anxious, because liftoff’s just the START… a BIG test is about to happen around a minute in, at a point called “Max Q” 

And this is why it’s important… so next time cheer with the engineers! 

If you think there should be more optimistic tech stories, subscribe!

#shorts #rockets #launch #space #engineer
title: Hardest Part of a Rocket Launch
